cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a unified end-to-end approach for anomaly detection on time-evolving data with high-dimensional categorical features without labeled samples. This involves combining Adversarial Autoencoder and Recurrent Neural Network, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, respectively. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
